text.section:
Except for an alternative testing protocol provided for post-accident victims under KRS 352.180(5) to (7), the minimum testing protocol acceptable for the establishment of drug-free status for certification under KRS Chapter 351 shall be at least a ten (10) panel urine test that shall include testing for the following substances:
Amphetamines;
Cannabanoids/THC;
Cocaine;
Opiates;
Phencyclidine (PCP);
Benzodiazepines;
Propoxyphene;
Buprenorphine;
Methadone;
Barbiturates; and
The remaining panels to be used in the urine test shall be set by order of the Mine Safety Review Commission no later than June 1 of each year.
